man I remember when I had to replace all HTTP calls in an old project w retrofit. Best part was someone wrote their own wrapper around apache and had a terrible API. ughhh.
One app I worked on used Volley for networking but still wrapped all the Volley calls in AsyncTasks.  :expressionless:

> we have a rather complex image serving system
Usually the problem
The moment you have to say this about anything, you are doing something wrong
things get complicated when you have terrabytes of images you need to serve
primarily: making sure you have good caching strategies
for example: we can serve album art in like 12-15 different (maybe more) resolutions
doesn’t make sense to deliver the max resolution every time, and it also doesn’t make sense to rescale on every request for one of the non-original size formats
and that’s just album artwork, we also serve band bio images, banner backgrounds, fan profile images, merch images, etc.. etc..
I know some app that downloads images and saves them as blob to sqlite >_>

I saw the creator of SQLite speak at a conference and he was saying that for blobs under a certain size, it can be faster to store/retrieve them from SQLite than it would as individual files in the file system
i think that size is something fairly generous too.. like 128kB
